<div2 type="caption">

<p>Negroe Chloe &amp; others<lb/>
vs<lb/>
Wm. Marbury.</p>

</div2>

<div2 type="body">

<p>Mordecai C. Fitzhugh makes oath that Chloe the Petitioner in this case was a slave of his deceased brother Richard Fitzhugh of Virginia, &amp; remained in his possession as a slave until within after years past, when he has understood, that she was sent by his said Brother Richard to his <del>said</del> (<del>said</del> Richards) son Richard Henry Fitzhugh then residing in George Town D. C.</p>

<p>Sworn in open Court 26th Apl 1822<lb/>
Wm Brent Clk</p>     
     
</div2>

</div1>
    
